{
  "texts": [
    "Deciding on retrospective harmonization means making comparable already existing and collected but heterogeneous data, some or none of which a given data scientist team may have themselves previously collected.",
    "To do so, data scientists must ensure that differences in technical formats (data syntax) and structure (data structure) of different datasets are resolved.",
    "They must further make comparable the meaning of different measures (data semantics).",
    "Once these dimensions are harmonized, then the different datasets can be combined and deduplicated if necessary.",
    "Meanwhile, deciding on prospective harmonization means coordinating on the same procedure for collecting data across multiple instances of data collection."
  ]
}